The paper deals with problems related to data structures (document exchange), information theory (error correcting codes), and computational complexity (analysis of sketch size and redundancy). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), followed by cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
